/* AUTO-GENERATED from config/ftbquests (legendaries.snbt + ultra_beasts.snbt +
 * paradox.snbt) for structure/item rituals, cross-referenced with Legendary
 * Monuments / other mods' actual recipes and lang tooltips, PLUS every
 * species' own "labels" field (real ground truth for who's restricted,
 * checked against kubejs/startup_scripts/catch_restrictions.js) and its
 * Cobblemon regional Pokedex membership.
 * Per species: category, region (home region, drives the Pika Star note
 * below, absent only for Melmetal/Meltan, which resolve to no region and so
 * skip that gate), structure (where/how to summon it, for real Legendaries
 * plus any MANUAL_RITUALS override), items (what's actually required,
 * generic candy rewards filtered out), each with its own recipe chain +
 * tooltip text where the game provides one, and an optional free-text note
 * for a ritual too specific to fit the structure/items shape (see
 * MANUAL_RITUALS, e.g. Magearna).
 *
 * REAL universal mechanic (verified directly in catch_restrictions.js, not
 * assumed): a Poké Ball can NEVER be thrown at a legendary/mythical/ultra
 * beast/paradox species outside of battle, for ANY of them, always. And a
 * battle against a wild one of these (or using an already-owned one in ANY
 * battle) is blocked entirely unless the player has completed a "Pika Star"
 * Summoning Ritual for that species' home region (10 regions, one ritual
 * each: defeat the ATM Team trainer series once, then ritual 4 "ancient"
 * balls + 4 Mega Stones + several already-owned Pokémon native to that same
 * region, at a Summoning Ritual Altar). This applies on top of whatever
 * species-specific method gets you INTO a battle with it: a real Legendary's
 * structure+item ritual, or an Ultra Beast's hourly Ultra Wormhole event (see
 * ultra_beasts.snbt's own quest text, NOT a plain bait-optimizable wild
 * spawn like the rest of this app models, it's a timed boss encounter).
 *
 * IMPORTANT, corrected 2026-07-22 (twice): MOST Legendaries/Mythicals/Ultra
 * Beasts/Paradox mons have NO functional wild spawn in the currently
 * installed pack. Their only spawn source anywhere is the paradox_spawns_ccc/
 * ub_spawns_ccc/legendary_spawns_ccc compat files, and kubejs/server_scripts/
 * Tweaks/disable_mons.js explicitly zeroes out every one of them via
 * ServerEvents.generateData at actual game launch, dynamically, invisible to
 * a plain file glob (extract_spawns.py replicates this override directly).
 * BUT 17 species are a deliberate exception: this pack RE-PUBLISHES their
 * spawn definition under the "cobblemon:" namespace (kubejs/data/cobblemon/
 * spawn_pool_world/*.json), which disable_mons.js's namespace-specific paths
 * never touch, so they keep a real wild spawn on top of the Pika Star gate:
 * Jirachi, Manaphy, Shaymin, Tornadus, Thundurus, Landorus, Diancie, all 4
 * Tapus, Necrozma, Zeraora, Kubfu, Zarude, Enamorus, Ogerpon. Caught only
 * because extract_spawns.py originally keyed its merge by bare filename
 * ("0385_jirachi.json"), which silently collapsed that cobblemon: namespace
 * copy and the disabled legendary_spawns_ccc: copy into the same slot; keying
 * by the FULL "namespace:spawn_pool_world/file.json" fixed it. 8 species
 * (Cosmoem, Lunala, Solgaleo, Naganadel, Phione, Silvally, Urshifu, Zygarde)
 * carry a restricting label but have NO quest chapter entry at all (mostly
 * evolution-only, not independently caught); included here anyway so the
 * Pika Star note still shows for them. */
